The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 EUROPEAN CLUB UPDATE 

United oppose Heinze move

Macau: Manchester United manager Alex Ferguson

 confirmed his opposition to Gabriel Heinzes move to Liverpool on Monday. He also said he was unhappy with the conduct of Heinzes

 agent in a seeming escalation of the dispute between the two Premier League

 rivals over the 29-year-old Argentine. 

He was responding to comments made earlier in the day by Liverpool manager Rafael Benitez who said he was confident the deal with Heinze would go through. 

Scholes surgery 

Macau: Manchester Uniteds Paul Scholes is to have an exploratory knee operation that will rule him out of the start of next season, the club said on Monday. The midfielder has been sent home from their Asian tour on Monday. 

City take-over 

Bangkok: Thailands former Prime Minister Thaksin Shinawatra has gained total control over the Manchester City, his lawyer said on Monday. (AGENCIES) 




